<p>
    NeuEve® Suppository
</p>

<p>
    Indication: Vaginal odor, dryness, atrophy, or painful intercourse (dyspareunia).
</p>

<p>
    Directions for use: Use restroom to empty bowels or the bladder. Wash hands with soap and water. Lie on back, raise
    knees and gently insert the suppository with a finger and push into the vagina as far as it will comfortably go.
    Keep the lay down position for about 15 min until the suppository melts. Using at bedtime is desirable. Use one for
    every 2-3 days. Do not use during menses. For more details of suppository application please see a video at
    [http://www.youtube.com/ watch?v=YEYheg3AEWY]
</p>

